JOHNNESBURG - Justice Minister Ronald Lamola is giving details about the correctional processes that are being followed now that Jacob Zuma is in jail. The minister is addressing a briefing on Thursday at the Estcourt Correctional Centre where the former president has started serving his 15-month sentence. Zuma was driven to the jail by convoy just before midnight, which was the deadline for police to arrest him. WATCH LIVE: Minister Lamola gives details of Zuma's arrest  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.